gonna have to wear a plaid skirt

04:23.179 --> 04:24.846
and kneesocks,
like Miss Bobbie.

04:24.847 --> 04:26.098
- Charley...

04:26.099 --> 04:27.182
- I saw him.

04:27.183 --> 04:28.684
His name's Mr. Davies.

04:28.685 --> 04:29.726
He's actually really cute.

04:29.727 --> 04:31.270
- And he's a poet.

04:31.271 --> 04:34.064
- Wait till he finds out
about Rebecca's dad.

04:34.065 --> 04:35.941
- Charley.
- Not cool.

04:35.942 --> 04:37.025
- No, not about that.

04:37.026 --> 04:39.027
About him being a famous poet.

04:39.028 --> 04:41.989
- He wasn't really famous.

04:41.990 --> 04:43.031
- Let's go play some hockey.

04:43.032 --> 04:44.366
- Let's not.
- Come on, yeah.

04:44.367 --> 04:45.826
That's exactly
what we need, yeah.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.619
- Seriously?
On the first day?

04:47.620 --> 04:50.414
Why do you have to kill me
on the first day?

05:00.300 --> 05:03.176
- Oh, I've longed
for these tubs.

05:03.177 --> 05:05.095
- I know, sometimes I hate it
so much when I'm here,

05:05.096 --> 05:08.557
but I just miss it all the time
when I'm at home.

05:08.558 --> 05:10.684
- How's your mom?

05:10.685 --> 05:13.395
- She just sat in her studio
and painted,

05:13.396 --> 05:16.648
listening to the same music
over and over.

05:16.649 --> 05:20.319
The same music my dad-

05:20.320 --> 05:22.654
my dad was listening to
when...

05:33.374 --> 05:35.917
- Rebecca, I want you to meet
a new girl, Ernessa Bloch.

05:35.918 --> 05:37.878
She'll be in the room
across the hall.

05:37.879 --> 05:39.713
Please help her
find her way around.

05:39.714 --> 05:40.756
- Sure.

05:40.757 --> 05:42.132
It's easy to get lost.

05:42.133 --> 05:44.343
Did they tell you this place
used to be a hotel?

05:44.344 --> 05:46.345
Um, like, 100 years ago.

05:46.346 --> 05:49.014
This place has a lot
of old nooks and crannies.

05:49.015 --> 05:50.557
- Breakfast is at 7:30,

05:50.558 --> 05:53.018
morning assembly 8:30 sharp.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.354
You must apply to me
for permission

05:55.355 --> 05:57.397
to leave the school grounds.

05:57.398 --> 05:59.775
You may use
one of two staircases

05:59.776 --> 06:01.443
to get to the dining room.

06:01.444 --> 06:04.071
The left one also goes
to the library.

06:08.242 --> 06:10.911
- It's so, so different
from the first time

06:10.912 --> 06:14.664
I came to Brangwyn
two years ago.

06:14.665 --> 06:17.834
My father had just died.

06:17.835 --> 06:21.046
My mother was a wreck.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.672
So I was sent here.

06:25.343 --> 06:32.849
♪ ♪

06:32.850 --> 06:36.520
Every night,
I sat in my room alone,

06:36.521 --> 06:39.147
aching for my father.

06:39.148 --> 06:41.983
And then I met Lucy.

06:41.984 --> 06:45.487
She was so confident,
carefree, and normal.

06:45.488 --> 06:48.990
She taught me
how to be happy again.

06:48.991 --> 06:51.159
That's why I love her so much.

07:04.966 --> 07:06.675
