07:23.025 --> 07:25.193
- Believe me,
I wish I was like you.

07:25.194 --> 07:26.862
- Good morning.

07:26.863 --> 07:28.738
It gives me great pleasure

07:28.739 --> 07:30.240
to welcome another
freshman class

07:30.241 --> 07:32.033
to Brangwyn school.

07:32.034 --> 07:34.786
- I scored.
Party in your room tonight?

07:34.787 --> 07:36.121
- Okay.
- Amen.

07:36.122 --> 07:40.125
- Your life here will be
a moral and spiritual journey

07:40.126 --> 07:43.253
that will prepare you
for whatever life awaits you

07:43.254 --> 07:45.338
outside these gates.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.969
- She's never going
to change that speech.

07:50.970 --> 07:52.053
- No.

07:52.054 --> 07:53.513
- Oh, I want to sign up
for practice.

07:53.514 --> 07:54.556
- Okay.

07:54.557 --> 07:56.016
I got to grab my books
for English...

07:56.017 --> 07:57.225
Check out
the cute new teacher.

07:57.226 --> 07:58.310
I'll see you at quiet hour?

07:58.311 --> 08:01.646
- I said I would
spend it with Dora.

08:01.647 --> 08:04.232
- It's our first day back.

08:04.233 --> 08:05.233
- Okay.

08:05.234 --> 08:07.319
I can see her another time.

08:07.320 --> 08:08.653
- Okay, great.

08:13.659 --> 08:14.993
- Hi.

08:14.994 --> 08:16.244
- Hi.

08:16.245 --> 08:18.830
- I'm Ernessa... Bloch.

08:18.831 --> 08:22.292
- Yeah, I saw you last night.

08:22.293 --> 08:24.294
How are you finding
everything?

08:24.295 --> 08:26.546
It's a little strange.

08:26.547 --> 08:27.589
- It must be hard,

08:27.590 --> 08:29.299
with everyone already
knowing each other.

08:29.300 --> 08:30.967
- What's that?

08:30.968 --> 08:33.135
- It's a friendship necklace.

08:33.136 --> 08:35.096
My friend Rebecca
gave it to me.

08:38.643 --> 08:40.477
- It's really pretty.

08:45.441 --> 08:46.775
Would you show me around?

08:46.776 --> 08:49.694
I don't really know
where I'm supposed to be.

08:49.695 --> 08:51.696
- Yeah.

08:51.697 --> 08:53.031
Yeah, come with me.

08:53.032 --> 08:55.367
- In all of the classic Gothic
horror stories,

08:55.368 --> 08:57.911
we see expressed
some kind of anxiety

08:57.912 --> 08:59.663
about the modern world.

08:59.664 --> 09:01.206
In Bram Stoker's Dracula,

09:01.207 --> 09:04.584
some critics see an anxiety
about female power,

09:04.585 --> 09:07.712
female sexuality,

09:07.713 --> 09:10.340
a fear that
the pure Victorian maiden

09:10.341 --> 09:12.509
would be transformed
into a ravenous beast.

09:12.510 --> 09:14.636
The story is a shape-shifter,

09:14.637 --> 09:17.430
just like the vampire itself.

09:17.431 --> 09:19.558
You find it in different forms
in almost all cultures,

09:19.559 --> 09:21.393
but there are three things
you find

09:21.394 --> 09:23.228
in every vampire story:

09:23.229 --> 09:27.691
sex, blood, and death.

09:33.531 --> 09:35.657
Becca?

09:35.658 --> 09:37.951
Just want you to know,
I'm a great admirer

09:37.952 --> 09:39.744
of your father's work.

09:39.745 --> 09:41.037
I'm going to be running
a poetry workshop

09:41.038 --> 09:42.038
later this term.

09:42.039 --> 09:43.039
I was hoping you'd take part.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.916
- Yeah.

09:44.917 --> 09:46.835
- Okay, good.

09:46.836 --> 09:49.504
- Um, thank you.

10:00.141 --> 10:01.349
