from your father.

15:17.750 --> 15:20.001
- I didn't inherit anything
from my father.

15:20.002 --> 15:22.420
- Are you sure?

15:25.090 --> 15:26.925
- I'll find another room.

15:32.890 --> 15:40.897
♪ ♪

15:45.194 --> 15:47.362
It's wonderful here, Daddy.

15:47.363 --> 15:50.865
- I wanted to show you
this place.

15:50.866 --> 15:52.700
- It's so beautiful.

15:52.701 --> 15:54.535
- It's always peaceful here.

15:56.747 --> 15:58.748
- I've missed our walks
so much.

16:01.710 --> 16:03.252
I thought I would never
see you again.

16:06.256 --> 16:08.383
- Don't be so sad, Rebecca.

16:08.384 --> 16:10.468
I'm always here.

16:10.469 --> 16:12.053
- I love you, Daddy.

16:29.822 --> 16:31.447
- Thank you for joining us,
Rebecca.

16:31.448 --> 16:33.199
- I'm sorry.
- That's okay.

16:33.200 --> 16:35.952
We're just talking
about CarmiIIa.

16:35.953 --> 16:37.787
Now, with Carmilla,

16:37.788 --> 16:39.414
we are looking at
one of the originators

16:39.415 --> 16:40.957
of the Gothic tale,

16:40.958 --> 16:43.376
20 years before Bram Stoker
wrote Dracula,

16:43.377 --> 16:45.294
and I think it's fair to say,

16:45.295 --> 16:46.963
it influenced him greatly.

